description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for candidates with Aseptic or Radiopharmacy background and clinical trial experience to join the Radiopharmacy team at the Royal Marsden NHS Foundation Trust, Sutton.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The brand new post offers an opportunity for an enthusiastic, self-motivated individual to develop their aseptic skills whilst contributing to running our comprehensive clinical Radiopharmacy service to the Trust and a number of external hospitals. The work of the Radiopharmacy includes dispensing and quality control of diagnostic and therapeutic radiopharmaceuticals, clinical trials, as well as provision of an In Vitro laboratory service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post-holder is required to work to extremely high standards of accuracy and must have a flexible approach to work. Major job roles include the production and QC of radiopharmaceuticals under the terms of the Manufacturers Specials licence and the IMP Manufacturer’s Authorisations held by the Radiopharmacy. The post holders will be supported by the operational team as well as the senior team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Successful applicants will be part of a friendly, supportive and experienced team that provides a Tc-99m service alongside high quality specialist services including a range of Ga-68 radiopharmaceuticals, complex Y-90 and Lu-177 therapeutic radiolabelling and clinical trials. The post holder will be expected to participate in the clinical trial work and development activities of the Department which provides an excellent opportunity for an ambitious Radiopharmacy technician to progress their skill set.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ideally, applicants must be a registered Pharmacy Technician (GPhC) and previous experience in radiopharmacy is desired. Candidates who hold a suitable degree in a related scientific discipline, a post-graduate qualification in Radiopharmacy or suitable aseptic experience may also be considered.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It is a requirement of the job that all staff are available to start work between 05:00 – 08:30 on a rotational basis.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Charlotte Monaghan, Principal Radiopharmaceutical Scientist, 020 8661 3308&lt;/p&gt;
